.TH ANNCHIVE 1 "March 2026" "AnnaChive v1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
annchive \- Local CLI tool for downloading open-access resources with Tor anonymity
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B annchive
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] \fICOMMAND\fR [\fIARGUMENTS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
AnnaChive is a command-line tool that helps you download free resources from the internet:
.IP \(bu 2
Research papers from arXiv, Semantic Scholar, PubMed
.IP \(bu 2
Books from Anna's Archive, Internet Archive
.IP \(bu 2
Code from GitHub
.IP \(bu 2
Academic papers via Sci\-Hub (requires Tor)
.PP
\fBKey Features:\fR
.IP \(bu 2
Download without donation \- uses public methods (BitTorrent)
.IP \(bu 2
Tor for restricted sources \- access blocked content
.IP \(bu 2
Encrypted storage \- your library, your data
.IP \(bu 2
Security\-first \- no logging, local\-only

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-debug\fR
Enable debug logging
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Show this help message and exit

.SH COMMANDS

.SS init
Initialize annchive with configuration.
.IP
\fBannchive init\fR [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.TP
\fB\-\-library\-path\fR \fIPATH\fR
Custom library location (default: ~/annchive_library)
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-encrypt\fR
Disable database encryption

.SS search
Search for resources across different sources.
.IP
\fBannchive search\fR \fISOURCE\fR \fIQUERY\fR [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.TP
\fB\-\-limit\fR \fIN\fR
Maximum number of results (default: 10)
.TP
\fBSOURCES:\fR
.RS
.TP
\fBarxiv\fR
Research papers (arXiv.org)
.TP
\fBgithub\fR
Code repositories (GitHub.com)
.TP
\fBsemantic\-scholar\fR
Academic papers metadata
.TP
\fBpubmed\fR
Medical/biological papers
.TP
\fBinternet\-archive\fR
Books, media, Wayback Machine
.TP
\fBannas\-archive\fR
Books, papers, Z\-Library
.TP
\fBscihub\fR
Papers (requires Tor)
.RE

.SS get
Download resources from various sources.
.IP
\fBannchive get\fR \fISOURCE\fR \fIID\fR [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.TP
\fB\-\-to\fR \fIDIRECTORY\fR
Output directory for downloads
.TP
\fB\-\-md5\fR \fIHash\fR
MD5 hash (for Anna's Archive)
.TP
\fBSource Examples:\fR
.RS
.TP
\fBarxiv\fR: \fIID\fR = arXiv ID (e.g., 1706.03762)
.TP
\fBgithub\fR: \fIID\fR = owner/repo-name
.TP
\fBpubmed\fR: \fIID\fR = PMID number
.TP
\fBinternet\-archive\fR: \fIID\fR = Archive identifier
.TP
\fBannas\-archive\fR: \fIID\fR = MD5 hash
.RE

.SS library
Manage your local collection.
.IP
\fBannchive library\fR \fICOMMAND\fR
.TP
\fBlist\fR [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
List all downloaded items
.RS
.TP
\fB\-\-limit\fR \fIN\fR
Limit results (default: 20)
.TP
\fB\-\-source\fR \fISOURCE\fR
Filter by source
.TP
\fB\-\-project\fR \fINAME\fR
Filter by project
.RE
.TP
\fBsearch\fR \fIQUERY\fR
Search within your library
.TP
\fBstats\fR
Show library statistics
.TP
\fBadd\fR
Add item to library manually
.RS
.TP
\fB\-\-source\fR \fIS\fR
Source name
.TP
\fB\-\-title\fR \fITITLE\fR
Item title
.TP
\fB\-\-author\fR \fINAME\fR
Author name
.TP
\fB\-\-format\fR \fIFMT\fR
File format (pdf, epub, etc.)
.TP
\fB\-\-path\fR \fIPATH\fR
File path
.TP
\fB\-\-project\fR \fINAME\fR
Project name
.TP
\fB\-\-tags\fR \fITAGS\fR
Comma-separated tags
.RE

.SS config
Manage configuration settings.
.IP
\fBannchive config\fR \fICOMMAND\fR
.TP
\fBshow\fR
Show current configuration
.TP
\fBset\fR \fIKEY\fR \fIVALUE\fR
Set a configuration value
.RS
.TP
\fBExamples:\fR
.RS
.TP
\fBannchive config set tor-enabled true\fR
.TP
\fBAnnchive config set library-path /new/path\fR
.RE

.SS tor
Manage Tor connection for anonymous access.
.IP
\fBannchive tor\fR \fICOMMAND\fR
.TP
\fBstatus\fR
Check Tor connection status
.TP
\fBenable\fR
Enable Tor routing
.TP
\fBdisable\fR
Disable Tor (use direct connection)
.TP
\fBnew-identity\fR
Get new Tor identity (new IP)

.SH ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
.TP
\fBANNCHIVE_ENCRYPTION_KEY\fR
Encryption password (REQUIRED for encrypted DB)
.TP
\fBANNCHIVE_LIBRARY_PATH\fR
Library storage path (default: ~/annchive_library)
.TP
\fBANNCHIVE_TOR_ENABLED\fR
Enable Tor by default
.TP
\fBGITHUB_TOKEN\fR
GitHub API token (for higher rate limits)
.TP
\fBNCBI_API_KEY\fR
PubMed API key

.SH FILES
.TP
\fI~/.config/annchive/config.json\fR
Configuration file
.TP
\fI~/annchive_library/annchive.db\fR
Encrypted SQLite database

.SH EXAMPLES

.SS First-time setup
.EX
$ export ANNCHIVE_ENCRYPTION_KEY='your-password'
$ annchive init
.EE

.SS Search and download a paper
.EX
$ annchive search arxiv "attention is all you need"
$ annchive get arxiv 1706.03762 --to ~/Papers/
.EE

.SS Clone a GitHub repository
.EX
$ annchive search github "python utilities"
$ annchive get github "owner/repo-name" --to ~/Projects/
.EE

.SS Enable Tor and download from Sci-Hub
.EX
$ annchive tor enable
$ annchive get scihub "10.1038/nature12373" --to ./papers/
.EE

.SS View your library
.EX
$ annchive library list
$ annchive library search "machine learning"
$ annchive library stats
.EE

.SH TROUBLESHOOTING

.SS "command not found"
.EX
$ pip show annchive
# or run directly
$ python -m annchive --help
.EE

.SS "Encryption key not set"
.EX
$ export ANNCHIVE_ENCRYPTION_KEY='your-password'
.EE

.SS "Download failed"
.EX
# Enable debug mode
$ annchive --debug search arxiv "test"

# Or enable Tor for restricted sources
$ annchive tor enable
.EE

.SS "Database locked"
.EX
# Close any other AnnaChive sessions and try again
.EE

